This paper deals with the issue of trustworthy AI in machine learning, specifically in the context of fair and robust training. The paper proposes a new method called FR-Train that addresses the problem of data bias and poisoning. Given that the paper focuses on machine learning and fairness, it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with issues related to AI and fairness, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the problem of data poisoning, which is a security issue, indicating that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of validation sets and crowdsourcing, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with issues related to bias and fairness, which could also place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
